"{\"uid\": \"washingtontimes.com-news-2024-jul-29-paris-olympics-tasteless-last-supper-transgression\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"OPINION:  On Jan. 7, 2015, two French Algerian brothers entered the Paris office of the satirical magazineCharlie Hebdo.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 120, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 31, \"end\": 46, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pied-Noir\", \"score\": 0.9998822878856958, \"rank\": 0.00011105003635132133, \"text\": \"French Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pied-Noir\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pied-Noir\"}, {\"begin\": 31, \"end\": 46, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pied-Noir\", \"score\": 0.9998822878856958, \"rank\": 0.00011105003635132133, \"text\": \"French Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pied-Noir\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pied-Noir\"}, {\"begin\": 68, \"end\": 73, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7825241881861024e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their rifles already leveled, the duo executed 12 employees and critically injured 11.\", \"from\": 121, \"to\": 207, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Kouachi brothers exacted revenge for a published cartoon of the Islamic Prophet Muhammad.\", \"from\": 209, \"to\": 302, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 293, \"end\": 301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muhammad\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.302856764964622e-13, \"text\": \"Muhammad\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muhammad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muhammad\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although not forbidden by the Quran, disparaging images of the prophet are considered profane and can elicit a violent response.\", \"from\": 303, \"to\": 431, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 333, \"end\": 338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quran\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.198794176803033e-45, \"text\": \"Quran\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quran\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On July 26, at the Olympic opening ceremony in Paris, Jesus was mocked in a drag-queen tableau of the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 433, \"to\": 547, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 480, \"end\": 485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7825241881861024e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 487, \"end\": 492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999707147258, \"rank\": 2.928507834680775e-08, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The role of Jesus, with a high, sparkly crown and immodest decollete, was played by a presumed beauty pageant winner, patently guilty of at least two deadly sins.\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 560, \"end\": 565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999707147258, \"rank\": 2.928507834680775e-08, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rep. Lauren Boebert, Colorado Republican, wrote on X: \\\"Mocking God at the Olympics is just disgusting.\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 814, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 717, \"end\": 731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lauren_Boebert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lauren Boebert\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lauren_Boebert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lauren_Boebert\"}, {\"begin\": 733, \"end\": 741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado\", \"score\": 0.9999999720325836, \"rank\": 2.749939191205185e-08, \"text\": \"Colorado\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado\"}, {\"begin\": 742, \"end\": 752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Spanish_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 1.7527521257074315e-13, \"text\": \"Republican\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Spanish_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Spanish_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Christians are constantly subject to this abuse.\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 815, \"end\": 825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9989007067300231, \"rank\": 0.0007339040984393754, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a complete disgrace to see on such a huge stage.\\\"\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 918, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the camera panned the long table of \\\"voguing\\\" luridly eye-shadowed disciples, particularly disturbing was not the bearded humanoid in a midnight blue bustier; it was the little brown-haired girl in dandelion yellow, sandwiched near the middle.\", \"from\": 920, \"to\": 1166, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Last Supper of Jesus took place approximately 1,465 years before Leonardo da Vinci painted his masterpiece.\", \"from\": 1168, \"to\": 1279, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1237, \"end\": 1254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0185786931448162e-32, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It took place during the Jewish celebration of Passover.\", \"from\": 1280, \"to\": 1336, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1305, \"end\": 1311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"score\": 0.8328365080703658, \"rank\": 0.2007158551644311, \"text\": \"Jewish\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\"}, {\"begin\": 1327, \"end\": 1335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passover\", \"score\": 0.9999999999918145, \"rank\": 8.04940285893407e-12, \"text\": \"Passover\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passover\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passover\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the eve of Jesus' crucifixion, Jesus broke a loaf of bread and said to his disciples, \\\"This is my body given for you; do this in remembrance of me.\\\"\", \"from\": 1337, \"to\": 1488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1351, \"end\": 1356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999707147258, \"rank\": 2.928507834680775e-08, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 1371, \"end\": 1376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999707147258, \"rank\": 2.928507834680775e-08, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He poured a cup of wine and said, \\\"This is the new covenant in my blood, which is poured out for you.\\\"\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1591, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These acts have been ritualized in the Catholic ceremony of the Eucharist, when congregants consume the symbolic body and blood of Christ and solemnly recall his excruciating torture and death - the merciless scourging, crown of thorns, spikes driven through his hands and feet, and Longinus' spear drawing blood and water from his side.\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1930, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1632, \"end\": 1640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.3704559791276885e-12, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 1657, \"end\": 1666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0404343856866263e-13, \"text\": \"Eucharist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Through this unimaginable suffering, Jesus took upon himself the sins of humanity so that each might have salvation and eternal life with God.\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 2073, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1968, \"end\": 1973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999707147258, \"rank\": 2.928507834680775e-08, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At this year's Olympic opening ceremony, the venerated Christian image of the Last Supper was hijacked for a cult movement's deviant political purposes.\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2227, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2130, \"end\": 2139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999746849951558, \"rank\": 2.531564555462004e-05, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With a little girl in its clutches, the cult gloatingly declared, \\\"We have your children.\\\"\", \"from\": 2228, \"to\": 2318, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, gender-bending indoctrination is embedded in public school curriculums across the United States, beginning in kindergarten.\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2410, \"end\": 2423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998150742784, \"rank\": 1.8492564334668775e-07, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But what is billed as benign gender affirmation is condemned as \\\"irreversibly harmful\\\" by the American College of Pediatricians.\", \"from\": 2452, \"to\": 2580, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The tasteless Olympic exhibition was not only an affront to 2.4 billion Christians but also was a transgression against moral decency.\", \"from\": 2582, \"to\": 2716, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2654, \"end\": 2664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9989007067300231, \"rank\": 0.0007339040984393754, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As evidenced in gay pride parades in cities such as San Francisco and Seattle, the LGBTQ movement has turned increasingly lewd.\", \"from\": 2718, \"to\": 2845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2770, \"end\": 2783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco\", \"score\": 0.9999999938781912, \"rank\": 6.121789832060002e-09, \"text\": \"San Francisco\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco\"}, {\"begin\": 2788, \"end\": 2795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seattle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.4880069196200004e-18, \"text\": \"Seattle\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seattle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seattle\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Public nudity and pornographic acts have become common, and moral objections are swiftly stifled by \\\"woke\\\" countercharges of some cancel-worthy iteration of \\\"phobic.\\\"\", \"from\": 2846, \"to\": 3012, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is curious that Christianity, a religion of peace, charity and forgiveness, was singled out for this burlesque and not, say, Islam.\", \"from\": 3014, \"to\": 3148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3033, \"end\": 3045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999193318837053, \"rank\": 8.067462433975049e-05, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France is home to approximately 6 million Muslims, make up more than one-third of Europe's entire Muslim population.\", \"from\": 3150, \"to\": 3266, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3150, \"end\": 3156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9998814374367367, \"rank\": 0.00010654402483270081, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3192, \"end\": 3199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.9989551836833108, \"rank\": 0.0010459090997607485, \"text\": \"Muslims\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}, {\"begin\": 3248, \"end\": 3254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.9988258898385343, \"rank\": 0.0011754903164195734, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many of them live in unassimilated enclaves that prioritize their religious doctrines and Shariah (Islamic law) over the statutes of polite French society.\", \"from\": 3267, \"to\": 3422, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3357, \"end\": 3364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sharia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shariah\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sharia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sharia\"}, {\"begin\": 3366, \"end\": 3377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sharia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.746296223510505e-16, \"text\": \"Islamic law\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sharia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sharia\"}, {\"begin\": 3407, \"end\": 3413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9983090266288379, \"rank\": 0.0016825091260635708, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The history of Islamic extremism is still a poignant memory.\", \"from\": 3424, \"to\": 3484, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3439, \"end\": 3456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_extremism\", \"score\": 0.7646868481126782, \"rank\": 0.30615111551550095, \"text\": \"Islamic extremism\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_extremism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_extremism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It does not take much imagination to visualize the Shariah-inspired response - in a country brimming with Kouachi-aged men - to an act blasphemous to Islam performed in front of the world.\", \"from\": 3485, \"to\": 3673, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"2024's Olympic opening ceremony was exploitative and disrespectful, but in keeping with Christian grace, it will be forgiven.\", \"from\": 3675, \"to\": 3800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3763, \"end\": 3778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grace_in_Christianity\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christian grace\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grace_in_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grace_in_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to Romans 12:18-19: \\\"Do all that you can to live in peace with everyone.\", \"from\": 3801, \"to\": 3883, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3814, \"end\": 3823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romans_12\", \"score\": 0.9999998994831054, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Romans 12\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romans_12\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romans_12\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dear friends, never take revenge.\", \"from\": 3884, \"to\": 3917, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Leave that to the righteous anger of God.\\\"\", \"from\": 3918, \"to\": 3960, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2022 Scott R. Hammond is a Boston resident.\", \"from\": 3962, \"to\": 4002, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3964, \"end\": 3969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"score\": 0.9999999977439984, \"rank\": 2.2529567549841803e-09, \"text\": \"Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\"}, {\"begin\": 3973, \"end\": 3980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hammond_organ\", \"score\": 0.9999964749930141, \"rank\": 2.3231939024637444e-06, \"text\": \"Hammond\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hammond_organ\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hammond_organ\"}, {\"begin\": 3986, \"end\": 3992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3624128412964115